<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-26T16:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-26T16:30:00-05:00" n="447" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.9331/75: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Secretary to the President</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sanders</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Superior, Wis.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-26T16:30:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">July 26,
                                        1928—4:30 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July
                                26—?]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President has approved and signed full powers for Minister MacMurray
                            transmitted with your letter 25th. Will be returned in pouch
                            tomorrow.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Everett Sanders</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>